My fiancé and I came here for his 25th birthday (boyfriend at the time/2 years ago!!) I made reservations 2 weeks prior and was able to get in a Sunday at 9 PM. We arrived earlier than our reservation but they sat us right away. First off, this is the classiest of the classiest & super fancy!! Bathrooms were so nice and clean. This is quiet fine dining. We both did the 4 course meal & ordered different things so we can try everything. They did start us off with a palate cleanser soup. The whole dinner took about 2 hours. All the dishes were superb. I loved the seared foie Gras and the lobster. My fiancé's lamb was delicious and I don't even care for lamb. Everything was so good. Service was great. They even gave us a dessert plate at the end on top of our ordered desserts & some little cakes to take home. We packed the extra dessert & cakes home as our little souvenirs. If you're willing to spend some $$$$$ and some time to enjoy delicious food on top of great service, I definitely recommend Gary Danko! I'll definitely come back for a super special occasion for sure.

Let me start off by saying... if I could give this place 10 stars I WOULD! It's takes a ton for me to say I Love Love a place all the way around! A little background... I printed the menu and gave it to my husband as a Xmas gift with reservations booked! The date came and we got done up and arrived to for our reservations! They seated us immediately at a very intimate table They dropped off the wine menu which for my husband and I was amazing! I HIGHLY recommend ordering at least half a bottle of wine. It's more bang for your buck and the choices are wonderful! Since it was our first time we had the server explain how the menu works... For $134 you can have ANY 5 things on the menu. That can be 5 apps, 5 entrees, 5 desserts!!! Or mix and match That alone is a bang for your buck! We did a mix of items so we both can cover most things on the menu. I have posted some pictures. You simply can't go wrong! I don't eat duck and I ate the duck. Everything was so flavorful and delicious. I will say once I got to the 4 course I couldn't even chew I was so full but couldn't stop because everything was to die for. I can't give enough compliments to this place. Absolutely delightful Hats off to the chef

Stopped by for amazing dinner at this spot...absolutely cannot lose here...every option is done to exception which is why they are Michelin star restaurant! The menu is easy to order from and you chose 3, 4 or 6 options from anything in the menu. This is the perfect place to go for a special occasion - I came for my birthday and the ambiance was amazing. We did have to wait to be seated however even though we made a reservation. They have a bar for you to wait at while your table is being prepared, which made up for the unexpected wait. The tables were decorated with roses and candles and the servers were extremely polite and helpful. They give you the option to choose between 3, 4, or 5 courses per person and scale down the food they give you if you choose more courses. I didn't expect there to be much food since swankier places tend to give really small portions but I was decently surprised. The servings were generous and was the perfect amount to allow you to try everything and enjoy it. We ordered the roast main lobster, the risotto with rock shrimp (recommended by the server), lemon pepper duck, seared filet of beef, pan seared bass, scallops, louisiana butter cake and creme fraiche cheesecake. The scallops were probably my favorite. They were the biggest scallops I'd ever seen and they were juicy and seasoned so well! I also really enjoyed the lemon pepper duck - they served the dish with two different portions of duck and you could taste a refreshing hint of lemon. I was disappointed by the risotto which came server-recommended. It was mediocre and wasn't anything too special. The beef was also disappointing - it was served with a sweet sauce and the medley between salty and sweet was offputting. I also really enjoyed the butter cake. I love sweets and the outside of the cake was pleasantly crispy and paired well with the gooeyness of the inside.

We came here a couple of weeks ago to celebrate my husband's graduation at 7pm on a Sunday evening. I made the reservations one month in advance. We arrived early so we can look for street parking instead of valet parking for $20. There's plenty as long as you give yourself some time to look. Since we arrived early and had about 45 minutes to kill, we walked down the street to Ghirardelli Square and ordered a frozen hot chocolate to share. It was very busy there but it allowed us to enjoy each other's company and enjoyed something sweet before dinner...haha We got back to the restaurant and got seated right away. The place is not that large so i see why reservations are needed. Many people go there for celebrations. The smaller tables are close together but still allows enough space for some private conversation. I love how they are not traditional with the menu. You can choose from a 3, 4 or 5 course menu and all the guests do not have to have same same number of courses!!! That is a win in my book because i can't eat as much as my husband can. He could eat enough for the both of us! But because the prices are very affordable, my husband convinced me to just get the 5 courses and whatever we had left over, we would take home. To say the least, i would've been happy with 3 courses. I took my filet and duck breast home. I literally only took a bite from each just to try. The servers were very sweet, they came to check on how we were doing and noticed i had barely touched my food. They got concerned that something was wrong. There was not, i was just stuffed. We were there for about 3 hours because the way they time everything. My husband thought we were eating too fast because we would be waiting so long in between each entree. Everything was good there, however, if you get the duck breast, they'll ask you how you want it cooked. We chose medium rare. If i was to pick again, I would ask for medium-medium well. It was so rare it was a little difficult to chew. Oh, the little pineapple cream cheese muffin they give you at the end as a souvenir is absolute delicious. I thought i wouldn't like it, so it took me a couple of days to finally open it...when I did i took the smallest little bite because I'm not really a dessert/sweets person but i basically scarfed it down in 30 seconds. It was sooo good!!! To all future guests, enjoy!

Gary Danko's is not an establishment normally on my radar as I tend to be more of a pub food person. It was a special occasion so I cleaned myself up and off we went to experience this fine dining venue. First off you can not deny the fantastic level of service at this relatively small venue. We ordered the 3 course meals which included the chicken tart (eh, tasted like pie crust and onions), risotto (excellent), beef filet (cook just right, average flavor), lamb (delicious but a bit jiggly rare for me, was billed as medium rare), the cheese plate (amazing cheeses) chocolate soufflé (super good), LA butter cake (fantastic). Due to our special event an additional cake and mini cookies were served gratis, a nice touch. UNIQUE & EXQUISITE EXPERIENCE A birthday celebration dinner can't get more extravagant than the custom experience you can have at Gary Danko. I love that you can opt to have everything picked out for you or you can pick what you like from the menu to have a 3, 4, or 5 course meal. The 5-course truffle menu looked appealing, but we opted to order 10 different items to share between the two of us. It was admittedly a little too much food and we should've done the 3 course meal. The birthday guy had foie gras, bass, venison, cheese, and the flamed bananas dessert. I enjoyed the seared tuna, lobster, beef, cheese, and chocolate soufflé. I would absolutely recommend the lobster, tuna, and CHEESE. This cart of cheese situation is so awesome and I wish I could've just ordered that and bread. We shared a bottle of wine recommended by the sommelier after each having a cocktail. The service was of course impeccable and unlike anything we have in our hometown. The party favor and bonus dessert was an extra hint of awesome for the next day at the end of our meal. If you have the means, an evening spent at Gary Danko is one you will undoubtedly enjoy.

Ah Gary Danko, one of the most coveted and highly rated restaurants in San Francisco. Because it is the higher end fine dining, this is the place where you go to celebrate special occasions or holidays. Gary Danko truly is a unique experience. Strengths include the stellar customer service, in which the waiters/waitresses ensure your water glass is filled, bread plate replenished, dishes and silverware changed in between courses, and of course, the good food. The food is also another unique experience. You have the option of going with the chef's tasting menu for a little more than $200, which includes a 5 course meal with appetizer and dessert. Or you have the option to create your own 3-4-5 course meal. Basically, you can order appetizer, 1-2 entrees, dessert, or you can order all entrees so you can try a bit of everything. I opted for the 3 course meal, ordering seared ahi tuna, seared filet of beef cooked medium, and the lovely delectable baked chocolate souffle. All dishes tasted delicious, with a good balance between savory and spices. The chocolate souffle was mouth-watering decadence. I honestly do not think you could go wrong with ordering anything here. My whole party enjoyed their dishes and desserts. It was truly a wonderful fine dining experience to remember for a long time!

Ambience was what you would expect from a restaurant like Gary Danko. My favorite flavors of the evening were the Coconut Thai Curry, Seafood Risotto and Glazed Oysters. Undoubtably I was on a quest for seafood that evening.

As usual, Gary Danko never disappoints. Great time with our besties, everything we ate was absolutely fabulous. My favorites of the night was the golden caviar, foie gras, seared scallops, roast maine lobster and the duck.

    We came here a couple of weeks ago to celebrate my husband's graduation at 7pm on a Sunday evening. I made the reservations one month in advance. We arrived early so we can look for street parking instead of valet parking for $20. There's plenty as long as you give yourself some time to look.

    Since we arrived early and had about 45 minutes to kill, we walked down the street to Ghirardelli Square and ordered a frozen hot chocolate to share. It was very busy there but it allowed us to enjoy each other's company and enjoyed something sweet before dinner...haha

    We got back to the restaurant and got seated right away. The place is not that large so i see why reservations are needed. Many people go there for celebrations. The smaller tables are close together but still allows enough space for some private conversation.

    I love how they are not traditional with the menu. You can choose from a 3, 4 or 5 course menu and all the guests do not have to have same same number of courses!!! That is a win in my book because i can't eat as much as my husband can. He could eat enough for the both of us!

    But because the prices are very affordable, my husband convinced me to just get the 5 courses and whatever we had left over, we would take home. To say the least, i would've been happy with 3 courses. I took my filet and duck breast home. I literally only took a bite from each just to try.

    The servers were very sweet, they came to check on how we were doing and noticed i had barely touched my food. They got concerned that something was wrong. There was not, i was just stuffed. We were there for about 3 hours because the way they time everything. My husband thought we were eating too fast because we would be waiting so long in between each entree.

    Everything was good there, however, if you get the duck breast, they'll ask you how you want it cooked. We chose medium rare. If i was to pick again, I would ask for medium-medium well. It was so rare it was a little difficult to chew.

    Oh, the little pineapple cream cheese muffin they give you at the end as a souvenir is absolute delicious. I thought i wouldn't like it, so it took me a couple of days to finally open it...when I did i took the smallest little bite because I'm not really a dessert/sweets person but i basically scarfed it down in 30 seconds. It was sooo good!!!

    To all future guests, enjoy!

    Gary Danko's is not an establishment normally on my radar as I tend to be more of a pub food person. It was a special occasion so I cleaned myself up and off we went to experience this fine dining venue.

    First off you can not deny the fantastic level of service at this relatively small venue. There were a half dozen conversationalist servers showing off their wares of wine, cheese and deserts.

    We ordered the 3 course meals which included the chicken tart (eh, tasted like pie crust and onions), risotto (excellent), beef filet (cook just right, average flavor), lamb (delicious but a bit jiggly rare for me, was billed as medium rare), the cheese plate (amazing cheeses)  chocolate soufflé (super good), LA butter cake (fantastic). Due to our special event an additional cake and mini cookies were served gratis, a nice touch.

    Overall we had a memorable and enjoyable experience and left appreciating the overall approach and professional efforts to make our life a little bit better.

    UNIQUE & EXQUISITE EXPERIENCE

    A birthday celebration dinner can't get more extravagant than the custom experience you can have at Gary Danko. I love that you can opt to have everything picked out for you or you can pick what you like from the menu to have a 3, 4, or 5 course meal. The 5-course truffle menu looked appealing, but we opted to order 10 different items to share between the two of us. It was admittedly a little too much food and we should've done the 3 course meal.

    The birthday guy had foie gras, bass, venison, cheese, and the flamed bananas dessert. I enjoyed the seared tuna, lobster, beef, cheese, and chocolate soufflé. I would absolutely recommend the lobster, tuna, and CHEESE. This cart of cheese situation is so awesome and I wish I could've just ordered that and bread.

    We shared a bottle of wine recommended by the sommelier after each having a cocktail. The service was of course impeccable and unlike anything we have in our hometown. The party favor and bonus dessert was an extra hint of awesome for the next day at the end of our meal.

    If you have the means, an evening spent at Gary Danko is one you will undoubtedly enjoy.

    Ah Gary Danko, one of the most coveted and highly rated restaurants in San Francisco. Because it is the higher end fine dining, this is the place where you go to celebrate special occasions or holidays. Gary Danko truly is a unique experience. Strengths include the stellar customer service, in which the waiters/waitresses ensure your water glass is filled,  bread plate replenished, dishes and silverware changed in between courses, and of course, the good food.

    The food is also another unique experience. You have the option of going with the chef's tasting menu for a little more than $200, which includes a 5 course meal with appetizer and dessert. Or you have the option to create your own 3-4-5 course meal. Basically, you can order appetizer, 1-2 entrees, dessert, or you can order all entrees so you can try a bit of everything. I opted for the 3 course meal, ordering seared ahi tuna, seared filet of beef cooked medium, and the lovely delectable baked chocolate souffle. All dishes tasted delicious, with a good balance between savory and spices. The chocolate souffle was mouth-watering decadence.

    I honestly do not think you could go wrong with ordering anything here. My whole party enjoyed their dishes and desserts. It was truly a wonderful fine dining experience to remember for a long time!
